{
  "- **dsv**: dsv is shutting down operations at a texas distribution center after losing a contract, with 391 workers affected. the denmark-based logistics provider said in a warn notice filed thursday that it will terminate all operations at a third-party logistics facility located at 101 mars road in wilmer, texas, with layoffs expected to begin april 30 or within two weeks of that date. operations are expected to continue under a different logistics provider, raising the possibility that some displaced workers may be rehired. this signals potential contract instability and facility churn relevant to dsv's broader logistics footprint. published: ~april 10, 2026": "2026-04-17T09:31:04.718127",
  "- **ford motor company**: ford said doug field \u2014 chief ev, digital and design officer \u2014 has \"elected to leave the company after a transition over the next month.\" ford said the new structure will integrate field's responsibilities with the company's global industrial operations. this sweeping leadership departure and reorganization\u2014merging the ev division into the core manufacturing structure\u2014signals strategic uncertainty and potential operational disruption. published: april 15, 2026": "2026-04-17T09:31:04.718433",
  "- **amazon**: amazon has denied media reports claiming around 14,000 more employees would be fired in may. this comes after the company confirmed 16,000 corporate layoffs in january 2026. while amazon denies a new round, ongoing workforce uncertainty and earlier corporate cuts remain a risk factor. amazon's warehouse/logistics operations continue to operate but under heightened scrutiny following a workplace fatality at an oregon warehouse reported april 14. published: april 8, 2026": "2026-04-17T09:31:04.718438",
  "- **anduril industries**: the u.s. army has awarded anduril industries a $16.8 million contract for hardware and components supporting its ghost-x small drone systems, the pentagon announced april 7, 2026. additionally, anduril and impulse space are moving into one of the most ambitious elements of donald trump's proposed golden dome missile defense system: space-based interceptors. these new contracts add to anduril's massive expansion trajectory, which already includes a $1 billion, 1.18-million-square-foot long beach campus announced in january. published: april 4\u20137, 2026": "2026-04-17T09:31:04.718449",
  "- **rocket lab**: rocket lab today announced it has completed the acquisition of mynaric ag, a leading provider of laser optical communications terminals for air, space, and mobile applications. the company paid $155.3 million consisting of a nominal cash payment and 2,277,002 shares of rocket lab common stock. rocket lab also announced it will release q1 2026 financial results on may 7, 2026. this acquisition deepens their space systems portfolio and long beach operational footprint. published: april 14\u201316, 2026": "2026-04-17T09:31:04.718455",
  "- **voyager technologies**: nasa and voyager technologies have signed an order for the seventh private astronaut mission to the international space station, targeted to launch no earlier than 2028 from florida. separately, voyager technologies has doubled its ability to produce propulsion systems for commercial and defense satellites out of its littleton facility compared to a year ago. the denver aerospace company took over the littleton facility after acquiring exoterra resource in october. strong expansion signals across production capacity and new government contracts. published: april 13\u201315, 2026": "2026-04-17T09:31:04.718460",
  "- **archer aviation**: archer aviation has achieved 100% federal aviation administration (faa) acceptance of its \"means of compliance\" for the midnight aircraft. archer aviation is drawing attention after achieving 100% faa means of compliance acceptance and signaling plans for type inspection authorization as early as 2026. this is a critical certification milestone\u2014archer is the first evtol company to reach this stage, bringing it closer to commercial launch and likely driving facility and workforce expansion. published: april 11\u201316, 2026": "2026-04-17T09:31:04.718466",
  "- **mach industries**: mach industries, a defense manufacturing company that develops advanced unmanned systems, today announced the appointment of amanda sustak as senior vice president of business development. (april 9, 2026) mach industries also announced the appointment of anand gopalan as chief autonomy and systems officer. (april 14, 2026) two senior executive hires in one week signals aggressive scaling of the huntington beach-based defense manufacturer, following its $100m series b. published: april 9 & 14, 2026": "2026-04-17T09:31:04.718468",
